    *   Since we want lexicographically smallest task names, the heap should compare `idxToName[a]` and `idxToName[b]`.
    *   `compare(a, b)`: return `idxToName[a] < idxToName[b] ? -1 : (idxToName[a] > idxToName[b] ? 1 : 0)`.
    *   Actually, since we just need the min, bubble up/down logic:
        *   Bubble up: `while (i > 0 && compare(heap[i], heap[parent(i)]) < 0) { swap; i = parent(i); }`
